    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I think nested types needs to be managed. Following code:\r\n\r\n```cython\r\ncdef list[list[int]] a = [[1]]\r\nprint(cython.typeof(a.pop().pop()))\r\nprint(cython.typeof(a[0][0]))\r\n```\r\nIs printing, what is not optimal:\r\n```\r\nPython object\r\nint\r\n```\r\n\r\nUpdate:\r\n\r\nThe issue is not related to nesting types (the reproducer works even for `list[int]` type). The issue is that when `.pop()` is called, Cython handles return value via\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/cython/cython/blob/87f82b7d7c84886396e15f0c09910011188047af/Cython/Compiler/ExprNodes.py#L6465\r\n\r\nThis function forces the return line to be pyobject:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/cython/cython/blob/87f82b7d7c84886396e15f0c09910011188047af/Cython/Compiler/ExprNodes.py#L6277-L6282\r\n\r\nI am inclined to leave this improvement to other PR...\r\n\r\n_Originally posted by @matusvalo in https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/7424#issuecomment-4364523936_\r\n            ",
